<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARCELLA CISNEY; TELEVISION AND THEATER DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marcella Cisney, 76, one of network television's first women directors, who 
also served as producer and director at the Pasadena Playhouse, Laguna 
Playhouse, and Las Palmas Theatre in Hollywood. She directed CBS dramatic 
programs in New York in the early 1950s and later staged operas for the New 
York City Opera Company. Married to arts administrator Robert Schnitzer, she 
lived in Weston, Conn., and was named one of 100 outstanding women of 
Connecticut in 1987. In Weston, Conn., on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
