<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTING WITH BOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Times handicapper Bob Mieszerski lost $60 when the front horse in his $10 
triple bets, Open Hand, ran third. Bob, who started the meeting with a mythical 
bankroll of $1,000, is now down to $897.30. This total reflects a $20 
adjustment for Sunday's bet when he selected a losing $10 exacta box on 
Nijinsky's Lover and Lucky Kate. However, There was no exacta betting on the 
race. 
</P>
<P>
Tor today, Bob's bet bet is a $20 parlay from Flippable in the fifth to Patchy 
Groundfog in the eighth. 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's Bankroll: $957.30 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's loss: $60.00 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll: $897.30 
</P>
