<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Integrated Resources Inc.: The financial services firm announced a 
second-quarter loss of $1.04 billion due to failing businesses and cheap asset 
sales in a bid to avoid bankruptcy. In the same period a year ago, the New York 
firm earned $12.8 million. Revenue in the current period totaled $70.6 million, 
down 38% from last year. The company said the loss exceeded a previously 
anticipated $600-million decline mainly because of substantially lower than 
expected proceeds from the sale of its core businesses to Los Angeles-based 
Broad Inc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
