<HEADLINE>
<P>
AND 'AFTER THE WALL,' WHAT OF SOCIALISM? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was delighted to read the extremely incisive, well-written "After the Wall" 
(Dec. 6). It did an excellent job of addressing a question that various family 
members and I have been batting around for several weeks, namely how Marxist 
professors are reacting to the worldwide celebration of communism's collapse in 
Eastern Europe. 
</P>
<P>
My cousin, a philosophy professor in Orange County, reports that his extreme 
leftist colleagues are basically laying low and maintaining a conspicuous 
silence. 
</P>
<P>
LORNA BREMNER 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara 
</P>
