Broadcast News: The BBC will teach Polish broadcasters Western radio and 
television techniques as part of Britain's $80-million aid package, it was 
announced Wednesday. Thirty-six broadcasters, chosen by Polish Radio and 
Television, will begin six-week training programs starting in February. The 
fund was authorized by Parliament in June after Polish leader Gen. Wojciech 
Jaruzelski's visit to Britain. CLAUDIA PUIG 
