<HEADLINE>
<P>
EASY-TO-MAKE EASY-TO-STORE HOLIDAY TREAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Since no one can predict just when guests will show up during the Christmas 
season, it's always a good idea to have plenty of snacks on hand for impromptu 
entertaining. 
</P>
<P>
Spiced Walnuts will keep well for up to two weeks when stored in an airtight 
container. These flavored nuts, accented with the exotic flavors of cumin and 
curry, also make great gifts. Pack them securely in glass jars or canisters and 
tie with a holiday bow. 
</P>
<P>
SPICED WALNUTS 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons butter or margarine 
</P>
<P>
4 cups walnut pieces 
</P>
<P>
1 1/2 tablespoons curry powder 
</P>
<P>
1 tablespoon ground cumin 
</P>
<P>
1 1/2 teaspoons salt 
</P>
<P>
1/2 teaspoon sugar 
</P>
<P>
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add nuts and saute 3 to 4 
minutes, tossing often. Stir in curry, cumin, salt and sugar. Saute, tossing 
frequently, 2 to 3 minutes. Cool, then store in airtight container up to 2 
weeks. Makes 4 cups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, SPICED WALNUTS 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Recipe 
</P>
</TYPE>
