<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
DEMOLITION FEES CONSIDERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has directed the city attorney to draft a measure that would 
levy fees on developers who demolish older, less expensive motels and hotels in 
the city's coastal zone. 
</P>
<P>
The fee would be about $8,000 per room demolished. The money would be used to 
build new affordable lodging with rooms going for about $57 a night. 
</P>
<P>
The state Coastal Commission already imposes such a fee for projects brought 
before it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
