<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
VOLUNTEER AIDES NEEDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The newly formed Consumer Housing Information Service for Seniors is looking 
for volunteers to help older people deal with housing problems. 
</P>
<P>
Volunteers will be given two days of training, beginning Jan. 16. They will be 
informed about a variety of options available to senior citizens, including 
shared housing, property-tax relief programs, home repair and weatherization 
programs, congregate care facilities, retirement communities, subsidized senior 
housing and home-equity conversion. 
</P>
<P>
The program is being sponsored by WISE Senior Services, an agency formerly 
known as Westside Independent Services to the Elderly, together with the 
county's Area Agency on Aging and the American Assn. of Retired Persons. 
</P>
<P>
Further information is available from Carol Sussman at (213) 394-9871. 
</P>
</TEXT>
