<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRANKLIN FACES GARFIELD IN BID FOR CITY TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Franklin High will attempt to win its third consecutive City Section football 
title when the Panthers meet Garfield in the Northern Conference championship 
game Friday night at 8 at East Los Angeles College. 
</P>
<P>
Franklin (11-1) is led by senior quarterback Santiago Alvarez, who has passed 
for 3,706 yards and 49 touchdowns -- both state single-season records -- and 
senior wide receiver Lamar Lovett, who has 88 receptions for 1,189 yards and 16 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
Garfield (10-1-1) is led by running back Hilario Espinosa, who has gained more 
than 2,000 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
