<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN ARRESTED IN CHURCH BURGLARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A young man was arrested in La Crescenta Tuesday night in connection with a 
burglary that may have been part of a series of break-ins at churches in the 
area. 
</P>
<P>
Police declined to give any details about the suspect or even to say exactly 
where he was arrested. His arrest resulted from the investigation of a burglary 
at a Montrose church in September. 
</P>
<P>
"He was traced through fingerprints that were found at the scene in Montrose," 
said Detective Jerry Starks of the Crescenta Valley Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
The series of burglaries has involved vandalism, theft and, in one instance, 
arson. 
</P>
<P>
Thefts in the series occurred on Sept. 20 at the Church of the Nazarene in 
Montrose, on Oct. 23 at the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in La 
Crescenta, on Oct. 28 at St. Bede's Church in La Canada Flintridge, on Nov. 25 
at the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in La Canada Flintridge, and 
on Dec. 5 at the First Baptist Church in La Crescenta. 
</P>
<P>
Office machines, cash or both were taken from each of the churches involved. A 
fire was also set at St. Bede's, causing an estimated $5,000 in damage to the 
office, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
