<P>
NEW CRACK FUELS OPPOSITION TO GARVEY RESERVOIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Metropolitan Water District of Southern California officials say they have 
almost remedied the flooding from the 41-acre Garvey Reservoir in Monterey 
Park, which damaged two homes on Fulton Drive. 
</P>
<P>
But Monterey Park officials are continuing to oppose the reopening of the 
reservoir, particularly since a second crack near its base was found this week 
about 1,000 feet from the first one. 
</P>
