<P>
LAW FIRM FOR CITY SELECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After deciding earlier this fall to drop Brown, Winfield and Canzoneri as the 
city's law firm, the City Council last week selected Wallin, Kress, Reisman, 
Price and Dilkes of Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
One of the firm's partners, Robert Kress, will serve as city attorney. A 1972 
graduate of UCLA law school, Kress, 42, also functions in that role for for 
Rosemead and Bradbury, and as assistant city attorney for Bell Gardens. 
</P>
