SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: CLAREMONT; 
</P>
<P>
CITY COUNCIL ELECTS MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Councilman Nick Presecan was elected by his council colleagues as mayor of 
Claremont Tuesday night, succeeding Alex Hughes, who died last week. 
</P>
<P>
Presecan, 49, is senior vice president at Engineering-Science Inc. in Pasadena. 
Diann Ring was named mayor pro tem. 
</P>
<P>
The council will meet at 7 tonight at City Hall to consider whether to leave 
the council seat vacated by Hughes' death open until the April municipal 
election or appoint a successor. 
</P>
<P>
The council also will discuss tonight a controversial proposal to levy a 
landscape and lighting assessment fee to raise $1.2 million a year, starting 
next July. The fee would cost homeowners about $90 a year. 
</P>
