</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Public Library will sponsor a series of lectures, "Quest 
for the Renaissance," at three San Gabriel Valley libraries in January: 
</P>
<P>
* The first lecture, "Alberti, Leonardo da Vinci and Michelangelo," will be 
presented by Loren Patridge of the history department at UC Berkeley. 
</P>
<P>
* "The Book and the Library" will be presented by Mary Kay Duggan of UC 
Berkeley. 
</P>
<P>
* "Rebirth of Music" by William Mahrt of Stanford is the third lecture. 
</P>
<P>
