<HEADLINE>
<P>
PICK OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Pasadena Dance Theatre will present "The Nutcracker" at San Gabriel Civic 
Auditorium, 320 S. Mission Drive, San Gabriel, 8 p.m. Friday and Saturday and 
Dec. 22 and 23; 2 p.m. Saturday, Sunday and Dec. 23 and 1 p.m. Dec. 24. General 
admission tickets range from $12 to $15. 
</P>
<P>
The ninth annual production will feature David Roxander, former first soloist 
with National Ballet of Canada, and Ann Marie DeAngelo, formerly with The 
Joffrey Ballet. Above is a pose from the Doll and Bear dance. 
</P>
<P>
The performance of the ballet classic is based on the original 1944 
choreography created by William Christensen for the San Francisco Ballet. 
</P>
<P>
The Pasadena Dance Theatre, founded in 1958 by Evelyn LeMone, is a nationally 
recognized regional ballet company that has received choreographic awards from 
the National Assn. of Regional Ballet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
