<P>
ENERGY DEPT. TO LIFT PLUTONIUM SECRECY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Department of Energy has made an unprecedented decision to release 
plutonium production figures covering 1944 to 1960 at the Hanford nuclear 
reservation in Richland, Wash. The data had been requested by a panel of 
scientists overseeing a study of possible health effects from past radiation 
releases at Hanford. Figures on the production of plutonium, a key ingredient 
of nuclear weapons, have long been among the nation's most closely guarded 
secrets because it was thought they could help an enemy determine the size of 
the nation's nuclear stockpile. 
</P>
