<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO BONUS, STRIKE HALTS VENEZUELA'S MAIN PORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CARACAS, Venezuela 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Workers have started a strike at Venezuela's main port of La Guaira, 16 miles 
north of the capital of Caracas, a union spokesman said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
"We have paralyzed activity until we get our end-of-year bonus and vacation 
pay," said Leonardo Marcano of the Workers Trade Union, which represents the 
2,853 workers who began their strike Tuesday. Negotiations on the pay demands 
were proceeding, a spokeswoman for the port authority said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
