<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLIDAY TREAT FOR DOUGHNUT, APPLE LOVERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For a delightful Christmastime treat try Golden Delicious Oliebollen. This 
fanciful snack resembles lumpy doughnut holes and is made with Golden Delicious 
apples. 
</P>
<P>
GOLDEN DELICIOUS OLIEBOLLEN 
</P>
<P>
1 cup milk 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons butter or margarine 
</P>
<P>
Sugar 
</P>
<P>
1/2 teaspoon salt 
</P>
<P>
1/2 cup warm water 
</P>
<P>
1 package dry yeast 
</P>
<P>
1 egg 
</P>
<P>
3 cups flour 
</P>
<P>
2 cups chopped Golden Delicious apples 
</P>
<P>
3/4 cup dried currants 
</P>
<P>
Oil for deep-frying 
</P>
<P>
In saucepan heat milk, butter, 1 tablespoon sugar and salt until just warm. 
Place warm water in large bowl and sprinkle with yeast. Stir until dissolved. 
Add milk mixture, egg and 1 1/2 cups flour. Beat until smooth. 
</P>
<P>
Stir in apples and currants. Add remaining flour and mix well. Cover and let 
rise in warm place 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk. Drop by 
teaspoonfuls into deep oil heated to 375 degrees. Deep-fry about 5 minutes or 
until golden. Drain on paper towels. Roll in sugar while still warm. Makes 
about 2 1/2 dozen doughnuts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, GOLDEN DELICIOUS OLIEBOLLEN 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Recipe 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121489-0170 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 148472 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 14, 1989, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
