<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARRIER TO STAY AT USC, SEAU UNDECIDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mark Carrier said Wednesday that he will stay at USC for his senior season of 
football, and while Junior Seau is undecided, he said he is also inclined to 
remain in school. 
</P>
<P>
Carrier, a consensus All-American strong safety, and Seau, an outside 
linebacker and the Pacific 10 defensive player of the year, have been 
considering making themselves available for the NFL draft in April. 
</P>
<P>
NFL observers say they would be first-round choices if they forsake their final 
year of eligibility. 
</P>
<P>
Carrier will be a fifth-year senior next season, having redshirted as a 
freshman. Seau is currently a junior, having lost his freshman season of 
eligibility because of the Proposition 48 academic rule. 
</P>
<P>
USC will play Michigan in the Rose Bowl game on New Year's Day. MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
