<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States, the Soviet Union and nine other countries signed an 
agreement to test each other's athletes for performance-enhancing drugs. 
</P>
<P>
Details for such testing will be worked out in separate bilateral accords 
between national federations, it was announced. The agreement also said the 
countries should share all information on doping tests and sanctions, support 
establishment of common penalties for use of drugs and develop joint 
educational and research programs. 
</P>
