<P>
BOOMING BUSINESS: The expected 10,000 delegates at the Western Cable Conference 
(D5) will pad an already record year for Anaheim convention business -- a cash 
cow that last year delivered $1.3 billion to the Anaheim area. . . . The city 
hosts close to 300 conventions a year and so far in 1989 has attracted 1 
million exhibitors and delegates -- the seventh straight year of increased 
attendance, according to the city's Visitor and Convention Bureau. 
</P>
