<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL/ADVERTISING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New Stores: The miles of aisles for Orange County shoppers keep stretching. 
</P>
<P>
Some of the latest entrants: Lingerie for Less has opened a new Irvine store -- 
its fourth in Orange County. The store, at Culver Drive and Barranca Parkway, 
joins other Lingerie for Less shops here in Huntington Beach, Cypress, and 
Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
And Antique Club has leased 15,000 square feet at McFadden Commerce Center, a 
home and office furnishings complex in Santa Ana. The Antique Club store in 
Santa Ana will be the only Southern California outlet. 
</P>
<P>
And ground has been broken on a new retail and office complex -- Mercado del 
Rio -- on La Palma Avenue in Yorba Linda. The 44,000-square-foot project, 
scheduled to open in the spring, will include Uli's Gourmet Market, Allstate 
Insurance, and Econo Lube 'N Tune. Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff 
writer 
</P>
