<P>
MISSION VIEJO POWER RESTORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Electrical service was restored early today to all of the 2,200 homes and 
businesses in Mission Viejo that lost power when an underground electrical 
cable failed, a Southern California Edison spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The blackout occurred at 10:22 p.m. Wednesday evening. Most of the affected 
homes had their power restored within an hour, all within an hour and 45 
minutes, SCE spokesman Steve Nelson said. 
</P>
<P>
"All of the load has been restored and we will be replacing the cable in the 
near future," he said. The rapid restoration of power was accomplished by 
switching circuits around the failed cable. 
</P>
<P>
The area affected was west of the San Diego Freeway, east of Madero Street, 
north of Los Alisos Boulevard and south of Alicia Parkway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
