BRADY UNDERGOES HIP SURGERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Treasury Secretary Nicholas F. Brady successfully underwent elective surgery 
today to replace his arthritic right hip, the department reported. 
</P>
<P>
It is uncertain when Brady will be released from the hospital, but recovery is 
expected to last three to six weeks, the official said. During that time, 
Deputy Secretary John Robson will serve as acting secretary. 
