<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION; 
</P>
<P>
MUSLIM GROUP VOWS TO KILL POPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIRUT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A little-known Muslim group today threatened to kill Pope John Paul II because 
it said he has supported Lebanon's rebellious Christian leader, Gen. Michel 
Aoun. 
</P>
<P>
The communique from the group, the Organization for the Defense of the 
Oppressed, also told the Roman Catholic envoy living in this country, Papal 
Nuncio Pablo Puente, to "leave Lebanon soonest." 
</P>
<P>
The statement was delivered to a Western news agency as the Pope was criticized 
by Lebanese leftists for failing to receive Arab mediators seeking to end the 
14-year-old civil war between Muslims and Christians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
