<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
REUTERS HAS NEW MAN IN HAVANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reuters said today that Pascal Fletcher, a 30-year-old Briton, has taken over 
as the news and information organization's chief representative in Havana. 
</P>
<P>
Fletcher moves to the post after two years as Reuters' correspondent in Zambia. 
His predecessor in Havana, Gilles Trequesser, was expelled July 2, charged with 
filing a fallacious report. Reuters rejected the accusation. 
</P>
<P>
Cuban authorities refused to reconsider their decision, but agreed to accredit 
a new Reuters representative. 
</P>
<P>
Few major Western media have permanent correspondents in Cuba, and none of the 
American newspapers or news agencies do. 
</P>
</TEXT>
