<P>
EXPOS OWNER MAY SELL BALLCLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTREAL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Montreal Expos owner Charles Bronfman said today he would consider selling the 
team but only if the purchaser agreed to keep the club in Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
The Expos owner responded to a report in this week's issue of Sports 
Illustrated that said Bronfman wants to sell and that a Florida investment 
group in Orlando or St. Petersburg might bid for the franchise early in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm thinking of selling, but not to just anyone," Bronfman said. "The most 
important thing for me is that the team stays in Montreal." 
</P>
<P>
The Expos have lost Mark Langston, Bryn Smith and Pascual Perez to free agency 
and replaced them with Joaquin Andujar, Oil Can Boyd and Dave Schmidt. 
</P>
<P>
"The Expos are run by good baseball men," Bronfman said. "Don't worry, we'll be 
there this year and we'll be more competitive than some people have been led to 
believe." 
