Photo, PREP ALL-STARS: This year's edition of The Times' Southeast All-Star 
High School Football Team is headlined by outstanding running backs from four 
area high schools: South Gate, Lynwood, Bell Gardens and Whittier Christian. 
Players on the first and second teams were announced today and will be honored 
at a brunch Sunday in Anaheim. ; Photo, Even when the Gahr High School defense 
was knocked down it held on, which was representative of Gahr's surprisingly 
successful season. In this fourth-quarter action, Danny Donisthorpe of Gahr, on 
ground, doesn't let go of Warren High's runner Derrick Brown. BARRETT STINSON / 
Los Angeles Times; Photo, Memo Watkins; Photo, Chris Anderson; Photo, Richard 
Brown; Photo, Aaron Rodts; Photo, Ruben Rodriguez; Photo, Ray Maldonado; Photo, 
Rudy Ramirez; Photo, Ivan Wilson; Photo, Ron Papazian; Photo, Charles Levy; 
Photo, Scott Alvarez; Photo, Jessie Carrillo; Photo, Chris Emch; Photo, Puna 
Peko; Photo, Raul Garcia; Photo, Mike Cardona; Photo, Kali Williams; Photo, 
Frank Ozuna; Photo, Valentino Hanks; Photo, Chuck Stafford; Photo, Travis 
Carter; Photo, Miguel Cortez; Photo, Carlos Martinez; Table, Southeast All Star 
Second Team, Offense ; Table, Southeast All Star second Team, Defense ; Table, 
